All Classes and Interfaces

Classes
Class
Description
FCFSQueue
Implements a simple First Come First Served (FCFS) scheduling queue.
FileParser
Reads process data from a text file and converts each line into a Process object for the MLQ scheduler.
Main
Main entry point for running the MLQ scheduling algorithm.
MLQScheduler
Controls the execution of the Multilevel Queue (MLQ) scheduling algorithm.
OutputWriter
Writes the results of the MLQ scheduling algorithm into a formatted text file.
Process
Represents a process in the system for the MLQ (Multilevel Queue) scheduling algorithm.
RRQueue
Implements a simple Round Robin (RR) scheduling queue.
SchedulerQueue
Abstract class that defines the general behavior of a queue within the Multilevel Queue (MLQ) scheduling algorithm.
